laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Laboratory examination of leukocytes and microorganisms
laboratory_examinations.findings: NO POLYMORPHONUCLEAR LEUKOCYTES SEEN. NO MICROORGANISMS SEEN.

The aorta and main thoracic vessels are well-opacified, normal caliber without evidence of dissection or intramural hematoma. Enlarged anterior mediastinal lymph node measures 1.2 cm. Streaky opacities in the dependent portions of lung, compatible with subsegmental atelectasis. A left lower lobe subpleural lung nodule measuring 5 mm. Diffusely hypodense liver consistent with hepatic steatosis.
